  "prompt": "What are some topics to talk about with someone you barely know?",
  "response": "Here are some good conversation topics for casual acquaintances:\n\n1. Safe, light topics\n- Current events\n- Local news\n- Weather\n- Weekend plans\n- Hobbies\n- Work or studies\n- Travel experiences\n\n2. Neutral questions\n- \"What do you do for work?\"\n- \"Are you from this area?\"\n- \"Have you lived here long?\"\n- \"What do you like to do for fun?\"\n\n3. Shared context topics\n- Where you met\n- Common friends/connections\n- Event/location you're currently at\n- Mutual interests\n\n4. Pop culture conversation starters\n- Recent movies\n- TV shows\n- Music\n- Sports\n- Popular podcasts\n\n5. Avoid controversial subjects\n- Politics\n- Religion\n- Personal finances\n- Deeply private matters\n\n6. Open-ended questions\n- \"What's keeping you busy these days?\"\n- \"Have you been working on any interesting projects?\"\n- \"What do you enjoy most about your job/studies?\"\n\nTips:\n- Ask follow-up questions\n- Show genuine interest\n- Listen actively\n- Keep conversation light and positive\n- Be prepared to share about yourself too",
